==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crinoline
<hw>Crin"o*line</hw> <pr>(kr?n"?-l?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>crin</ets> hair,L. <ets>crinis</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
kind of stiff cloth, used chiefly by women, for underskirts, to expand
the gown worn over it; -- so called because originally made of
<xex>hair</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A lady's skirt made of any stiff material; latterly,
a hoop skirt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crinose</ent>⟦br⟧
